    "body" : "<p>Andreas Lundgren's answer worked and I was able to compile and run my app.  </p>\n\n<p>However, when I tried to run the project's associated JUnit tests I received the same error.  Running </p>\n\n<pre><code>gradle -version\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>from Windows command prompt showed that gradle was still picking up the incorrect jdk.  To fix it I had to set the <code>JAVA_HOME</code> environment variable to point to the correct jdk and restart IntelliJ. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7596761,
      "reputation" : 81,
      "user_id" : 5762715,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Q_cFsaCoI0w/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAVQI/xV66IKCyXDw/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Aziz Mamoyan",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5762715/aziz-mamoyan"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1452258226,
    "last_edit_date" : 1452258226,
    "creation_date" : 1452255698,
    "answer_id" : 34677051,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Change in <code>pom.xml</code> <code>1.6</code> to <code>1.8</code></p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;plugin&gt;\n    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n    &lt;configuration&gt;\n        &lt;source&gt;1.8&lt;/source&gt;\n        &lt;target&gt;1.8&lt;/target&gt;\n    &lt;/configuration&gt;\n&lt;/plugin&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 246003,
      "reputation" : 944,
      "user_id" : 519859,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 64,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/YxuRc.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Java_Waldi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/519859/java-waldi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1459842603,
    "creation_date" : 1459842603,
    "answer_id" : 36420204,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For Gradle users having this issues, if nothing above helps this is what solved my problem - apply this declarations in your build.gradle files:</p>\n\n<pre><code>targetCompatibility = 1.6 //or 1.7;1.8 and so on\nsourceCompatibility = 1.6 //or 1.7;1.8 and so on\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Problem solved!</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1798484,
      "reputation" : 915,
      "user_id" : 1650469,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c9ab487a8702dddad576eb7c2a0e83d6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "B5A7",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1650469/b5a7"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1475793977,
    "creation_date" : 1475793977,
    "answer_id" : 39906775,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For Grails users, apply these declarations in your BuildConfig.groovy file:</p>\n\n<pre><code>grails.project.target.level = 1.6 //or 1.7;1.8 and so on\ngrails.project.source.level = 1.6 //or 1.7;1.8 and so on\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6440480,
      "reputation" : 21231,
      "user_id" : 4990642,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 53,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Z49N4lYm.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Soner from The Ottoman Empire",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4990642/soner-from-the-ottoman-empire"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1498827963,
    "creation_date" : 1498827963,
    "answer_id" : 44847232,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>It can be simply overcome by setting on <code>Project Structure</code>. You just need to select the right path for related version of JDK. Select <code>new</code> on dependencies tab, and choose the path. It's done!</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/P84ZS.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/P84ZS.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11077428,
      "reputation" : 21,
      "user_id" : 8133702,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-KfWQ2cqm7cQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAYs/Mj0J5yXHP_Q/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Katherine Nicol",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8133702/katherine-nicol"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1501600230,
    "creation_date" : 1501600230,
    "answer_id" : 45441525,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You need to click to the project\nOpen Module Settings and change the path of your JDK, if in the file POM you use jdk 1.8, configure jdk 1.8 with correct path.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4835491,
      "reputation" : 5025,
      "user_id" : 3902339,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/OmtOl.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "ArifMustafa",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3902339/arifmustafa"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1519303663,
    "creation_date" : 1519303663,
    "answer_id" : 48927826,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I checked all above said project version, module version, project bytecode version, target bytecode version settings in <code>IntelliJ Idea</code>, but all were the same as I scratched.</p>\n\n<p>I face this error <strong><code>Error:java: invalid source release: 1.8</code></strong> in <code>IntelliJ Idea 2017.2.6</code> because I upgraded the dependency version <code>Maven</code> pom file, which(dependency) were supposed to build for JDK 1.8 application and I were building my application on and with maven compiler source and target JDK 1.7.</p>\n\n<p>Hence I again downgrade the dependency version to earlier one in <code>Maven</code> pom, and the error gone after project Rebuild Module 'xyz_project'.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5850578,
      "reputation" : 1575,
      "user_id" : 4609353,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://graph.facebook.com/948029148549696/picture?type=large",
      "display_name" : "Oleg Ushakov",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4609353/oleg-ushakov"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1563301526,
    "creation_date" : 1563301526,
    "answer_id" : 57063367,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I add one more path unmentioned in this answer <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/26009627/4609353\">https://stackoverflow.com/a/26009627/4609353</a></p>\n\n<p>but very important is Edit Configurations</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4stEZ.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4stEZ.png\" alt=\"one more path\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2348623,
      "reputation" : 76,
      "user_id" : 2058104,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Mr0Ti.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "cresclux",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2058104/cresclux"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1590284684,
    "creation_date" : 1590284684,
    "answer_id" : 61980669,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I tried out all the steps mentioned in here <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/26009627/2058104\">https://stackoverflow.com/a/26009627/2058104</a>, but the 4th point has now changed. You need to go to <strong>Preferences -> Build, Execution, Deployment -> Compiler -> Java Compiler</strong></p>\n\n<p>In there, as shown in below figure, you need to change the \"Target bytecode version\". Although, I changed it to 8 (since I needed to downgrade to Java 8), it was giving the same error, over and over. Therefore, <strong>try to remove the existing entry (in this table) and add it again. This worked for me.</strong></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/K0LQR.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/K0LQR.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<p>On the other hand, clean the project and try to run again.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2817888,
      "reputation" : 376,
      "user_id" : 2422456,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 68,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/gXJre.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Derek MC",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2422456/derek-mc"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1598887730,
    "creation_date" : 1598887730,
    "answer_id" : 63673717,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had the same issue the solution for me was to change my java version in the pom.xml file.</p>\n<p>I changed it from 11 to 8.\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/l8CxC.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/l8CxC.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3691593,
      "reputation" : 1128,
      "user_id" : 3074057,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/kWsh7.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Beezer",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3074057/beezer"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1601915491,
    "creation_date" : 1601915491,
    "answer_id" : 64212651,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Lots of good answers.\nFor those using the (almost) latest version of Intellij, at the time of writing, what can be said, is that the project JDK can be at a higher level, than that of the module.\nIn fact without it, Maven will have to be rolled back to an older version.\nTherefore with the following version of Intellij:\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/MCo16.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/MCo16.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>One should not change the project level JDK and therefore be able to leverage the Maven or Gradle settings when building, but when running Maven or running Gradle using a more modern version of the JDK.\nIf you lower your project level JDK from say JKD8 to JDK6, Maven or Gradle will not run.</p>\n<p>Keeping your module at a lower level JDK-wise will enable you to build it to that version, if you use the Module rebuild or build options; using the menu options for rebuilding the project will complain wit &quot;Invalid source release:8...&quot;.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 17295469,
      "reputation" : 177,
      "user_id" : 12526239,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/01d120ee9621f75984592451b9c519f1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Yasin Bekar",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/12526239/yasin-bekar"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1602466246,
    "last_edit_date" : 1602466246,
    "creation_date" : 1602463889,
    "answer_id" : 64310393,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>As Andreas mentioned all about:</p>\n<pre><code>Error:java: invalid source release: 8 in IntelliJ\nError:java: invalid source release: 13 in IntelliJ\nError:java: invalid source release: 14 in IntelliJ...\n</code></pre>\n<p>OR whatever version you are using in Java...</p>\n<p>The problem will exist if you do not have it matching inside the below code:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;properties&gt;\n    &lt;maven.compiler.source&gt;1.8&lt;/maven.compiler.source&gt;\n    &lt;maven.compiler.target&gt;1.8&lt;/maven.compiler.target&gt;\n&lt;/properties&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>This 1.8 in my case, must be matching on your device through MAVEN project library, settings, preferences, project setting and SDK.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 18824073,
        "reputation" : 337,
        "user_id" : 13729422,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fd8e13015a3ff759f93a66e48055334d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
        "display_name" : "Uzair",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13729422/uzair"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1603642413,
      "post_id" : 64525877,
      "comment_id" : 114094932,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "If you don&#39;t SDK 12. Just add the latest one"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 18824073,
      "reputation" : 337,
      "user_id" : 13729422,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fd8e13015a3ff759f93a66e48055334d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Uzair",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13729422/uzair"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1603642240,
    "creation_date" : 1603642240,
    "answer_id" : 64525877,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I was recently facing the same problem.\nThis Error was showing on my screen after running my project main file.\n<strong>Error:java: invalid source release: 11</strong>\nFollow the steps to resolve this error</p>\n<ol>\n<li>File-&gt;Project Structure -&gt; Project</li>\n<li>Click New button under Project SDK: Add the latest SDK and Click OK.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/qRMIE.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/qRMIE.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>After running You will see error is resolved..</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/094W1.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/094W1.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 17184860,
      "reputation" : 71,
      "user_id" : 12439656,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AAuE7mCpkKiSh2g-nM5Y8KYkPw8zX4xu5PZyDfZ2d8MYiA=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "Raj Kushwaha",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/12439656/raj-kushwaha"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1626102201,
    "creation_date" : 1626102201,
    "answer_id" : 68349666,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If You Get This ERROR: <strong>Error:java: invalid source release: 12</strong>\nInformation:java: Errors occurred while compiling module 'IdeaProjects'\nInformation:javac 1.8.0_211 was used to compile java sources\nInformation:Module &quot;IdeaProjects&quot; was fully rebuilt due to project configuration/dependencies changes\nInformation:7/12/2021 8:21 PM - Build completed with 1 error and 0 warnings in 6 s 323 ms\nError:java: invalid source release: 12</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/AJvN5.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/AJvN5.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>THEN</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/br7Bx.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/br7Bx.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a>\nSelect Your Previous Version Project</p>\n<p>In My side :</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/rz99d.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/rz99d.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>FINISHED</strong></p>\n<p>If you Get SOlution of Your IDE then Message Me <a href=\"http://www.betechnical.tech\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">www.betechnical.tech</a>\nor amankushwaha9918@gmaill.com</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2508599,
      "reputation" : 430,
      "user_id" : 2181576,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/eb6a2bf94f604cf100e34a0520c9874d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "veritas",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2181576/veritas"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1642743573,
    "creation_date" : 1642743573,
    "answer_id" : 70796869,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my case the nuance was that I got a invalid source release 11 (instead of OP's 8). I tried all the solutions above</p>\n<ul>\n<li>gradle jvm version , java compilter bytecode version, module language.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I set all the above to java 8 (or 1.8) as that is the library I have on my machine.</p>\n<p>The issue was that the build.gradle file had</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sourceCompatibility = '11'</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Changed this to 8 and it stopped throwing 'compile failed invalid release 11' error</p>\n<p>solution reference: <a href=\"https://github.com/gradle/gradle/issues/12803\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">github forum</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8617529,
      "reputation" : 121,
      "user_id" : 6453791,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 40,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/OM2x7.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "N. I. Md. Ashafuddula",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6453791/n-i-md-ashafuddula"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1677562333,
    "creation_date" : 1677562333,
    "answer_id" : 75588193,
    "question_id" : 25878045,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I am using <strong>JDK 1.8.0_131</strong> and for my case the issue was <strong>Error:java: invalid source release: 12</strong>,\nI solved this by changing the version code <code>&lt;version&gt;2.7.5&lt;/version&gt;</code> in <strong>pom.xml</strong> and <code>module -&gt; language level 8</code>.</p>\n<pre><code>    &lt;parent&gt;\n        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-parent&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;version&gt;2.7.5&lt;/version&gt;\n        &lt;relativePath/&gt;\n    &lt;/parent&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
  "owner" : {
    "account_id" : 1370050,
    "reputation" : 20229,
    "user_id" : 1305516,
    "user_type" : "registered",
    "accept_rate" : 59,
    "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/fGuXb.png?s=256",
    "display_name" : "David says Reinstate Monica",
    "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1305516/david-says-reinstate-monica"
  },
  "is_answered" : true,
  "view_count" : 384253,
  "protected_date" : 1522664031,
  "accepted_answer_id" : 26009627,
  "answer_count" : 19,
  "score" : 412,
  "last_activity_date" : 1714873202,
  "creation_date" : 1410900043,
  "last_edit_date" : 1714873202,
  "question_id" : 25878045,
  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/25878045/errorjava-invalid-source-release-8-in-intellij-what-does-it-mean",
  "title" : "Error:java: invalid source release: 8 in Intellij. What does it mean?",
  "body" : "<p>I'm trying to compile some code that I have in IntelliJ Ultimate 13.1.4, but I get the following error, and I have no idea what it means:</p>\n<pre><code>Information:Using javac 1.7.0_55 to compile java sources\nInformation:java: Errors occurred while compiling module 'Example'\nInformation:Compilation completed with 1 error and 0 warnings in 3 sec\nInformation:1 error\nInformation:0 warnings\nError:java: invalid source release: 8\n</code></pre>\n<p>My guess is that it's something related to Java 8 vs Java 7, but I have no idea what specifically. I've tried to Google around for this message, but they either talk about <code>javac</code> or <code>target release</code>, so it doesn't exactly seem to apply.</p>\n"
}